 Abbey Church, Isle of Sheppey, Kent":"Isle of Sheppey, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Eastchurch, Kent, England":"Eastchurch, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Shurland House, Eastchurch, Kent":"Eastchurch, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Shurland House, EastChurch, Kent, England":"Eastchurch, Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Shurland","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Sharland in Morchard Bishop (Devon). The origin of the placename is uncertain."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Geoffrey","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic (Frankish and Lombard) origin, introduced to Britain by the Normans. It was in regular use among the counts of Anjou, ancestors of the English royal house of Plantagenet, who were descended from Geoffrey Plantagenet, Count of Anjou (  1113–51 ). It was a particularly popular name in England and France in the later Middle Ages; notable bearers in England include the poet  Geoffrey Chaucer  (  <i>c.</i>1340–1400 ) and in Wales the chronicler  Geoffrey  of Monmouth (  d. 1155 ). The original form and meaning of the name is disputed. According to one theory, it is merely a variant of   Godfrey ;  others derive the first part from the Germanic word <i>gawia</i> ‘territory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Geoffrey de Shurland was born about 1200 as the son of Adam de Shurland. He married Marjory de Kent in 1254, in Eastchurch, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1280, in Eastchurch, Kent, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 81, and was buried in Isle of Sheppey, Kent, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1200–1280":"umbes 1200–1280","1200–1280":"1200–1280","1234–Female":"1234–Surnud","1250–1313":"1250–1313","1250–1319":"1250–1319","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","Abt 1250":"umbes 1250","1313":"1313","1234":"1234","1200":"1200","1254":"1254","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1250":"1250","1160":"1160","1319":"1319","1280":"1280","St Sexburga Abbey Church, Isle of Sheppey, Kent":"Isle of Sheppey, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Eastchurch, Kent, England":"Eastchurch, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shurland House, Eastchurch, Kent":"Eastchurch, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shurland House, EastChurch, Kent, England":"Eastchurch, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1200–1280":"noin 1200–1280","1200–1280":"1200–1280","1234–Female":"1234–Kuollut","1250–1313":"1250–1313","1250–1319":"1250–1319","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","Abt 1250":"noin 1250","1313":"1313","1234":"1234","1200":"1200","1254":"1254","about 1200":"noin 1200","1250":"1250","1160":"1160","1319":"1319","1280":"1280","St Sexburga Abbey Church, Isle of Sheppey, Kent":"Isle of Sheppey, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Eastchurch, Kent, England":"Eastchurch, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shurland House, Eastchurch, Kent":"Eastchurch, Ken